AFFIRMATIVE.

88
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:28,055
[INDISTINCT
CHATTERING]

89
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:29,931
SECTION OPERATIONAL
READY.

90
00:06:30,057 --> 00:06:32,267
INTERESTING.

91
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:34,686
YOUR EARTH PEOPLE
GLORIFY ORGANIZED VIOLENCE

92
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:36,271
FOR 40 CENTURIES,

93
00:06:36,395 --> 00:06:40,025
BUT YOU IMPRISON THOSE
WHO EMPLOY IT PRIVATELY.

94
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:43,362
AND, OF COURSE,
YOUR PEOPLE
FOUND AN ANSWER.

95
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:46,948
WE DISPOSED
OF EMOTION, DOCTOR.

96
00:06:47,074 --> 00:06:49,368
WHERE THERE IS
NO EMOTION...

97
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:50,952
THERE IS NO MOTIVE
FOR VIOLENCE.

98
00:06:51,078 --> 00:06:53,454
[DOORS OPEN]

99
00:06:57,042 --> 00:06:59,044
WHERE'S THE CAPTAIN?

100
00:07:01,546 --> 00:07:04,383
WHICH ONE OF YOU
IS THE CAPTAIN?

101
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:05,633
I'M CAPTAIN KIRK.

102
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:19,022
MY NAME IS...

103
00:07:21,942 --> 00:07:23,651
VAN GELDER.

104
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:27,781
I WANT ASYLUM.

105
00:07:27,906 --> 00:07:29,616
AT GUNPOINT?

106
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:34,871
I WANT
YOUR PROMISE FIRST,

107
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:37,165
YOUR WORD THAT YOU WON'T
TAKE ME BACK THERE--

108
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:39,334
TO TANTALUS.

109
00:07:56,935 --> 00:07:58,979
NO PROMISES.

110
00:07:59,104 --> 00:08:00,814
GIVE ME THE WEAPON.
NO!

111
00:08:02,274 --> 00:08:03,317
NO...

112
00:08:03,442 --> 00:08:06,278
